programmes.show_description: Divided We Fall. Days after the shocking arrival of a new team member, division among the remaining six survivalists deepens as Russell leads the men on a risky two-day hunting trek. S2, Ep6
Left Behind. A violent two-day storm descends on the jungle. Before it's over, one more survivalist will be gone, leaving another hanging by a tenuous thread. S2, Ep7

Apple Barn. The team heads to Winchester, Virginia, to salvage an abandoned orchard barn, but they must pick through years of trash and treasures before they can begin. S9, Ep10
Saving A Gem. The crew finds a gem with a log cabin tucked inside an old farmhouse, but they struggle to disassemble and demolish the property due to the ever-increasing mud. S9, Ep11
This Means War - Part 1. Two monster dredges duke it out on the Bering Sea as a war brews between Shawn and Kris. Vernon's diver bleeds on his ascent. S11, Ep3
This Means War - Part 2. Two monster dredges duke it out on the Bering Sea as a war brews between Shawn and Kris. Vernon's diver bleeds on his ascent. S11, Ep4
Jacqui and Andrew pioneer new gold-hunting ground at Fish Creek. Rookie prospector, Kat, removes an old stump from the middle of the Brumbie's lease. S9, Ep10
Fear. In Airlie Beach, Julia catches two venomous snakes and releases them back into nature. Then, her next mission is an eastern brown snake. S1, Ep3
Lockout. After battling freezing spray, colossal waves and sub-zero temperatures, it's a race to harbour to offload their haul. But the immense arctic ice pack stands in their way. S5, Ep11
See the best of the monster seas, boat-crushing ice, scary rescues, wallet-stuffing crab pots, fights, and selfless heroism from the world of Deadliest Catch.
Plummer's Gold. Josh sets off to search for the lost fortune of a notorious Montana sheriff. During his investigation, Josh blows open a mine that's been sealed for over a century. S3, Ep1
Mysteries Of Bermuda Triangle. Josh Gates dives into the mysteries of the Bermuda Triangle. He goes to the ocean floor, the skies and space to explore its intriguing disappearances. S6, Ep10
Revealing The Triangle. To conclude his epic investigation, Josh Gates uses cutting-edge technology to investigate the Bermuda Triangle's most infamous shipwreck and lost flights. S6, Ep11
Subarctic S.O.S. The Raneys answer an urgent call from central Alaska, where they find a family with all the infrastructure but minimal skills to realize their dream. S5, Ep3
Blue Fire Opal Or Bust. Justin recruits his fiancé after admitting he's facing financial disaster. Plus, the Fire Crew face deadly snakes and the Cooke Brothers go down deep. S2, Ep8
Race Against Time. The Rookies battle busted hoses and finally hit treasure. Meanwhile, at their wash plant, the Cooke Brothers race to beat the worst drought in a decade. S2, Ep9
Carpe Diem. A new face joins the fold - 23-year-old Sean Dwyer fighting for the legacy of his father. Plus, Captain Keith's life spirals, and Sig torments his old protégé. S12, Ep1
The crew fly in to treat a surfer having a heart attack. They also face a battle against the Cornish weather to rescue a pensioner in distress. S2, Ep1
The flying paramedics tend to a gardener in trouble and a patient with a unique medical history. Plus, they're faced with a worrying head injury. S2, Ep2
The Poseidon Crew recruit a 14-year-old worker to help speed up their operation. Meanwhile, the Gold Timers are slowed down by a freak dust storm. S6, Ep15
The Final Fight. After a shock exit, the remaining survivalists face a brutal two-day water extraction journey. Electric eels, anaconda and caiman all pose threats in this finale. S2, Ep8
Eye Of The Storm. A wild child and retired sergeant are stranded in the Belize jungle after a catastrophic hurricane that threatens their entire challenge. How will they get on? S3, Ep2

Taylor Family Farm. The team heads to Yorktown to pick through an old farm and former Native American settlement. Mike and Tay handle the heavy lifting outside to save a steel boat. S9, Ep12
Marine Salvage. Mike and Robert head to Florida and get lessons in diving and safety so they can salvage under water. They recover old ship parts from the bottom of the ocean. S9, Ep13
Russian Roulette. Cornelia co-captains, Josh and Casey, risk a 500-mile trek north to the Russian line. Meanwhile, captain Keith struggles with a broken boat and a broken heart. S15, Ep10
Curse Of The Russian Line. The winter season strikes the fleet with brutal Storm Elsa. And, Josh and Casey haul their all-time biggest pots, starting a gold rush to the Russian Line. S15, Ep11
Hell Hath No Fury. The wrath of Arctic storm Elsa hits the Cornelia hardest as a breakaway pot thrashes Josh and Casey's crew. And, the icy blasts threaten to capsize the Wizard. S15, Ep12
Sixty Foot Monster. As arctic superstorm Elsa intensifies, a rare forecast warns of huge waves. Trapped in the crab-rich northern grounds, one boat faces a 60-foot monster. S15, Ep13
Bad Luck. The Opal Whispers are forced to leave behind a rich opal seam in a mine on the verge of collapse. The Cheals are cut off from their mine by crippling floods. S6, Ep5
Start Again From The Beginning. Gale force winds threaten the Digi Diggers' dreams of an eco-mine. The Bushmen discover dangerous old workings while clearing out their new mine. S6, Ep6
Hit Or Miss. The Mooka Boys may lose a potential investor due to their little mining progress. Disaster strikes for the Opal Whisperers when Sofia's hoist fails. S6, Ep7
Thrill Of The Hunt. Pete and Kyle take the biggest gamble of their season, hunting valuable Tourmaline crystals. Hugh and Jarrin tackle the world's only Stitchtite quarry. S1, Ep6
Deadly Crocs - Dangerous Air. The Rockhounds hunt a rainforest river system by crocodile-infested waters. Plus, Jarrin and Hugh confront low oxygen levels and crumbling mine walls. S1, Ep7
Crystal Climax. In the final week of the season, Patrick gets an offer for their million-dollar Amethyst cluster while his team race to unearth $200,000 of crystals. S1, Ep8
The Gold Gypsies could be sitting on a fortune but must decide whether to take a huge gamble. A water shortage halts Shane and Russell's operations. S5, Ep10
The Goldtimers hire a 7-tonne loader to end their gold drought. The Dust Devils risk running out of water. Marcus vanishes while clifftop detecting. S5, Ep11
The Poseidon Crew hunts for bush gold. The Gold Gypsies face a tough decision. The Victoria Diggers' perseverance could finally pay off. S5, Ep12
Is That A Goat? Donny has been to jail twice because of his hoard. And while Joyce sees comfort in her doll collection, everyone else sees a creepy obsession. S3, Ep6
Tiny Monsters. Sherry's hoard has broken up her marriage. Now, authorities are threatening to take away her children and condemn her home. Can she break her bad habits? S3, Ep10
Mischievous Duende. Paranormal investigators capture a shadow figure in a haunted Nevada prison. A tiny elfin creature makes a toddler uneasy in Argentina. S6, Ep6
Lost Souls Of Kingman. The crew investigate an Arizona high school plagued by troubling paranormal experiences. Is this linked to an abandoned cemetery buried beneath the building? S20, Ep15
Old Bullion Plaza School. The crew unlock the dark secrets entombed in the walls of an old school. During the investigation, they capture some of their best evidence in years. S20, Ep16
